description: This special edition features early appearances of Golden Age greats Fiery Mask, Mister E and Rockman — stars of J. Michael Straczynski and Chris Weston’s bestselling, critically acclaimed epic THE TWELVE! Collecting material from Daring Mystery Comics #1-2 (January-February 1940), The Human Torch #2 (Fall 1940) and USA Comics #2-3 (November 1941-January 1942).

With great powers comes great pain! Big City Comics welcomes DC Comics' artist Mark Sparacio who takes over the reigns as Ian's life enters a new chapter. Realizing that Ian can now access the full power of The Totem but not being able to control those powers puts his parent's soul in greater jeopardy. Plus, someone gets a serious 'beat down!'
name: With Great Power Comes Great Pain

description: It's Halloween, and the Scarecrow is on the prowl!  But nothing can scare the Super Friends!
name: Nothing To Fear

description: Zombies, zombies, zombies! The gang's got their work cut out for them, with two tales of zombie mayhem. Plus, a group of rival mystery-solvers falls on their tails!
name: The Terror Of Transylvania;  Mad Science; The Perilous Pendulum

description:
Retelling the first issue in the Hack/Slash series, this comic, as the title implies, is focused on new readers of the adventures of Cassie Hack and his partner Vlad.

But hardcore fans might enjoy it as well, not only for the new cover, but for the Slasher diary. It's a way of remember all the adventures of this team against the vicious slashers but from Cassie's own point of view. And of course, the characters profiles is a great bonus, just like the slashers gallery.
name: New Reader Halloween Treat!

description:
Doctor Doom is planning world domination and has developed clever schemes to accomplish that.  
 
He lures Superman and the Hulk into battling each other, the result of which frees the Parasite from his cell. Of course, Spiderman too jumps into the fray but is unable to offer any help. S.T.A.R. Labs takes Bruce Banner for treatment after his defeat, from where Doom plans to capture the Hulk later.  
 

Job flip

!  
Clark Kent goes to work with The Daily Bugle, while Peter Parker applies for The Daily Planet. Kent tries to please J.J.Jameson while Peter sweats it out with Steve Lombard.
 
Sometime later, Superman visits Doom in his

Embassy

, but Doom intends to capture Superman. However, Superman tricks him and escapes. 
 
Spiderman discovers the Metropolis branch of Doom's Project Omega and runs into Wonder Woman. Unknown to each other, they start fighting. Doom uses this chance to capture Wonder Woman. Spiderman escapes. 
 
Ther is always the thing with villain alliance, they try to kill each othe to gain power. Doom plans to use the energy-enhanced Parasite as fodder for his Project Omega, while Parasite intends to kill him.  
 
However, their plans do not succeed. They oppose each other, while the heroes destroy Project Omega (Doom's

super-reactor

). Parasite is recaptured, while Doom escapes. The Hulk too escapes his confinement.
name: DC and Marvel Present Superman and Spider-Man

volume.name: DC and Marvel present  Superman and Spider-Man

description:
Features Include:
The Ladies' Man!
Heads in the Clouds
Paper Caper
Knock It Off!
A Tired Left Arm
The Bitter Baby Sitter
Yea Team
The Milky Way!
name: The Ladies' Man!

description: A man is killed by a mysterious creature, his body drained of blood. A woman is savagely attacked by a ferocious beast, her jugular ripped out. Bat wings flutter across the moon and the howl of a wolf echoes through the streets, for the creatures of the night have risen from the grave, and humanity’s only salvation is the combined might of The Last Son of Krypton and The Dark Knight Detective. Blood will run red when Superman and Batman face off against vampires and werewolves for the fate of the entire DCU!
name: Seize the Night

volume.name: Superman and Batman vs. Vampires and Werewolves

name: The Case of the Dope Smugglers

description: The taste of revenge is the only thing that keeps this vampire alive. A pack of monster killed their family, and now the same course is what makes him strong, cleaning the streets as he waits to find the vampire who took everything from him.

The tournament begins and the best fighters around the world are more than ready to climb to the top. Everyone of them has an own reason to win it. Some are there for the glory of victory, others for the thrill of the battle, others will sacrifice everything just for payback. 

 In the end, someone has a score to settle, and the tournament is nothing but an excuse to begin the never-ending battle.

name: Bring Me the Head of Superman or the City Dies!! So Swears Krater, the Demolishing Man!!

description: The Road to Nowhere!
name: The Road to Nowhere!

description: Find out how Mercy Sparx, a Devil Girl hired by the big shots in Heaven to secretly take down rogue angels, got to Earth. Serendipity, a muse turned DeeJay battles it out with our unlikely heroine. It's either succeed and get a free pass through the pearly gates, or fail and risk going somewhere much worse.

Overview

The dead are restless. Rather than wait for judgment, they have escaped the afterlife and are forcing themselves into the bodies of the living. Reincarnation rapists, joyriders, they use their new bodies with abandon, leaving shattered lives in their wake. When government security is compromised by the possession of an intelligence community insider, the Atheist is called in to turn back an invading army of lost souls.
name: Incarnate, Part 1

description:
Overview

The bodies of the living are being hijacked by the restless spirits of the dead and the government has called in Antoine Sharpe to investigate. Driven by rational principles, Sharpe sets out to prove the cases of possession are merely a new disease. He consults the only man smarter than himself, a brilliant doctor whose entire body has been consumed by an aggressive, seemingly sentient form of cancer. But will Sharpe live long enough to learn the truth?
name: Incarnate, Part 2

description:
Overview

Sharpe and Nguyen are on the run. The possessed, real or not, are organized and wish to snuff out Sharpe's investigation before he can reveal the truth. Sharpe arms himself with a weapon even the dead will fear, but will he survive long enough to use it?
name: Incarnate, Part 3

description:
Overview

52 writer Mark Waid makes his Cthulhu Tales debut with a macabre story that gives retailers and fans a glimpse of the future of BOOM!’s entire horror line! Plus: writer Mark Sable (GROUNDED, FEARLESS) creeps in with his take on the Lovecraft mythos, and the terrors he’s seen will take your breath away!

Stories:

  • In The Pi Of The Beholder by Mark Waid
  • There Will Be Blood by Mark Sable
name: In The Pi Of The Beholder

description: A follow-up to the hit Cthulhu Tales and Cthulhu Tales: The Rising Lovecraft anthologies! A new volume featuring all-new stories from the best that horror comics offers! Spotlighting Brendan Hay, writer on The Daily Show! Includes six all-new, all-original tales of weird darkness and the macabre from the only comic book company you can trust to deliver a quality horror anthology!
name: Just a Photographer; Black Sun; Waiting for Cthulhu; What Lies Beneath; Respect your Elders; Bowels of the Desert; Happy Little Boy

description:
A sequel to the sold-out Cthulhu Tales one shot, featuring the same roster of writers: Eureka the TV show creator Andrew Cosby, Eureka show writer Johanna Stokes, Second Wave writer Michael Alan Nelson, Transformers screenwriter John Rogers, Ninja Tales writer Chris Ward, and a new creative voice in the mix: Hans Rodionoff, the writer of Marvel's Werewolf By Night movie and the upcoming Tekken film! Featuring the best of the best of a brilliant roster of artists, Cthulhu Tales: The Rising is a primal journey into a dark arena of horror.

Stories Titles

  • I Hear The Call by James Kuhoric
  • Are You There, Cthulhu? It's Me, Margaret. by Henry Alonso Myers
  • Seed Of Cthulhu by Christopher E. Long
  • The Pull Of Insanity by Hans Rodionoff
  • For You by Michael Alan Nelson
  • The Art Of Noises by Kevin Church
name: I Hear The Call; Are You There, Cthulhu? It's Me, Margaret; Seed Of Cthulhu; The Pull of Insanity; For You; The Art of Noises

description: From the creator of 52 and Annihilation, Keith Giffen! An alien microbe, traveling through space, arrives on Earth and discovers humanity. As it enters an array of innocent human bodies, it remakes them into something new. Something powerful. Something wanting its own homeland, its own dominion. A new mini-series depicting the battle between ordinary humans and this new, alien invader taking over human bodies and infusing them with untold power!

Overview

The virus rages. Ordinary men are transformed by something greater, something much more, an alien predatory intelligence hungry to assert... its dominion. In the face of this threat, an ordinary man must find a way to combat the menace and stop it. In a world without superheroes, how can a single man make a difference? An alien invasion told from a decidedly different perspective!

Overview

Chicago is in flames. Citizens lie dead in the streets. And the authorities have discovered that the threat isn't the superhumans that walk their metropolitan area wantonly killing people, it's the possible spread of the virus. As quarantine is ordered, panic spreads, causing even more fear and destruction. Armageddon has come to Chicago, and threatens to spread across the planet!

name: In all the old familiar places...

description:
Overview

Chicago is further torn apart, even as the authorities struggle to contain the virus - no one can get in, no one can get out, and as a result, no cavalry is coming. Just the same,salvation seems to be coming in the form of a vaccine and a cure - but is it too late to save Dick?

Overview

Dick has fallen to the virus. Chicago lies in wreckage and flames. Has this alien Dominion succeeded in conquering the earth? The conclusion of this powerful new series!

Overview

The Enigma Cipher – Nazi Germany used this mysterious machine to decrypt and encrypt their communications during the war. Now, in the present, a history professor gets his hands on an Enigma encrypted file that's been lost since WWII -- grad student Casey cracks it, and the professor and other people involved in her project show up dead. The secrets that it holds are the key to uncovering Nazi spies hidden at the highest level of government positions since WWII -- and a far-reaching plan of global, political and economic domination that's still in effect.

Overview

On the run now, Casey races to uncover the contents of the Enigma Cipher, however the contents are attracting the attention of black ops assassins and the FBI. What secrets does the Federal Bureau of Investigations hold, and how are they connected to the encrypted cipher that everyone seems to want?

The beginning of a brand new story arc and a great place for new readers to jump in. A teenage girl mysteriously appears in the Arkham jail with prophecies of doom. Arkham's Sheriff must decide if she's crazy or a harbinger of the evil that pervades the town.
name: The Gray Man, Part 1 of 4: Lucifer

description: Continuing a brand new story arc! Sheriff Raymond Dirk hunts for the killer that only teenage Lucy has seen! Can Sheriff Dirk find the mysterious 'Gray Man' before he kills again? Or are Lucy's prophecies of doom destined to come true?"
name: The Gray Man, Part 2 of 4: Circle of Friends

description: As Lucifer and the Sheriff continue their search for the elusive Gray Man, they find themselves the hunted rather than the hunters. Either way, they must stop the Gray Man or the Cthulhu cultists will have their way...and that can't be good for mankind's survival.
name: The Gray Man, Part 3 of 4: Lost and Found

description:
The final showdown between the Gray Man and Lucifer over the fate of mankind and the otherworldly conflict that could consume us all! What horrible price has the Sheriff paid to tip the balance in our favor? Will it be enough to save humanity? The answers are here - but the ongoing adventures of the FALL OF CTHULHU cast will continue next month in FALL OF CTHULHU: GODWAR!

Bonus: Text stories from Fall of Cthulhu fiction contest winners, the Roncoli Brothers!
name: The Gray Man, Part 4 of 4: Closure

description:
Overview

The year is 2013. Astronaut Don Maggert's first solo manned space flight has him disappear in the grip of an intergalactic horror. Returning to earth, he's been transformed into something that will throw the entire planet into peril!
name: Book One

description:
Overview

Maggert is fully transformed now, and the nation's military can't stop him. The world's only hope seems to rest in... a buried Nazi robot? And will Maggert's wife be able to talk him out of his massive rampage?
name: Book Two

description:
Overview
Milo is a slacker in this world, but the next parallel world over, he's the super-hero, Captain Valor! Valor's world has been destroyed, and now he's moved in with Milo. How is Captain Valor going to fit in to a world that doesn't have super-heroes? And how is Milo going to deal with finding out that Valor's girlfriend Steffie is the super-villain, Caliginous? And what happens when Caliginous makes a romantic play… for Milo?
name: Getting To Know You

description:
Overview
Captain Valor starts going for Milo's girl Stephie, while Milo starts to think Valor's arch-enemy Caliginous is pretty hot.
name: He Said, She Said

description:
Overview
With his back against the wall, Captain Valor finds his limits put to the test and he has to do something he has never done before in his super-hero career. Is he even capable of stepping up to the plate?
name: Zap! Pow! Bam!

description:
Overview

Award-winning mystery novelist Gary Phillips came to BOOM! with the best idea they'd heard yet. THE SOPRANOS was the soap opera of upper-class mob life. What do you get, Gary asked, when you transplant that tension to the African-American gangs in inner-city L.A.? Answer- you get the story of CQ, a young man who thought the mob was his family, until it turned on him, forcing him to fight against California's crime families to stay alive!

Overview

A direct market comic book event! The writer of the Academy Award-winning film Ray comes to comics in a big way, kicking off a new series at BOOM only! Stockbroker Lincoln "Linc" Greer, divorced dad, is looking forward to a hot date in a remote cabin for the weekend. When his date cancels and he gets stuck with visitation rights with his son, he takes the boy hunting in the wilds of Oregon. Before he knows it, his son is kidnapped and a voice at the other end of his cell phone tells him to do what he asks - if he ever wants to see his son again! Linc soon finds that he's the only African-American man in this small mostly white logging community. Isolated and alone, he's got to face a contentious community and save his son! A blockbuster thriller featuring artwork from new sensation Talajic, fresh off Image Comics' Deadworld!

Overview

Stockbroker Lincoln "Linc" Greer, divorced dad, now discovers that he is alone and in pain. His son gone - vanished - how does he find the clues he needs to save him? Where does he begin his search? And why won't this predominantly white small town help him? Is his son kidnapped... or dead?

Overview

It starts when stockbroker Lincoln "Linc" Greer, divorced dad, is acquitted of the murder of his son by the local authorities. Meanwhile, who have they picked up in the woods? Is it the kidnapper? It's becoming clear the entire town's in on it - if Linc talks to the wrong person, it could jeopardize his son's life!

Overview

Lincoln Greer finds himself fending for his life in the woods of Menifee. Chased by the corrupt citizens, he must figure out how to escape, and get his son back alive. From award-winning screenwriter James L. White comes this tense drama that examines racism in the hidden comers of America.
